nginx-beanfire-module CHANGES
=============================

Release 1.1.0 — 2026-06-07
---------------------------

Bug fixes:

  *) Fix: NULL pointer dereference when a request arrives without a
     User-Agent header. r->headers_in.user_agent was dereferenced
     unconditionally; it now falls back to "-" as with referer and user.

  *) Fix: global socket descriptor gmsofd was zero-initialized, causing
     dup2() to silently replace file descriptor 0 (stdin) with the
     beanstalk socket. The descriptor is now initialized to -1 and
     assigned directly from the connected socket without dup2().

  *) Fix: race condition between the keepalive thread updating gmsofd and
     worker request handlers calling send() on it. All access to gmsofd is
     now serialized with a pthread_mutex. Handlers skip the send when
     gmsofd is -1 (disconnected).

  *) Fix: EPOLLERR events were silently ignored with a bare continue,
     leaving the module sending to a broken socket indefinitely. EPOLLERR
     now triggers the same reconnect path as EPOLLRDHUP/EPOLLHUP.

  *) Fix: beanf_server.len was set to sizeof("localhost") which includes
     the null terminator, violating nginx ngx_str_t convention. Changed to
     sizeof("localhost") - 1.

  *) Fix: inet_pton() was called with gmconf.beanf_server.data which is
     not guaranteed to be null-terminated. The address is now copied into a
     local null-terminated buffer before the call.

  *) Fix: socket() errors in ngx_http_beanfire_connect() on the
     setsockopt() and non-blocking fcntl() paths did not close the newly
     created socket before returning, leaking a file descriptor on each
     failed connect attempt.

Changes:

  *) The keepalive thread socket is now set to non-blocking (O_NONBLOCK)
     before being registered with epoll, which is required for correct
     edge-triggered (EPOLLET) behavior.

  *) Replaced the deprecated epoll_create(size) call with
     epoll_create1(EPOLL_CLOEXEC). The size argument has been ignored by
     the kernel since Linux 2.6.8; EPOLL_CLOEXEC prevents fd leakage
     across fork/exec.

  *) Removed unused #include <poll.h>. The module uses epoll exclusively.

  *) Replaced #include <pthread.h> with static gmsofd_mutex initialized
     via PTHREAD_MUTEX_INITIALIZER, eliminating the need for runtime mutex
     initialization.
